abstract: The station with ICOS code BE-Lon is called Lonzée and located in the Vallonia part of Belgium, in the Province of Namur, Hesbaye region. It is a cropland of 11.8 ha that has a 4-year rotation between sugar beet (Beta vulgaris L.), winter wheat (Triticum aestivum L.), potato (Solanum tuberosum L.), and winter wheat (Triticum aestivum L.).
